header.gameNote: BIG TEN MEN'S TOURNAMENT - 1st ROUND AT INDIANAPOLIS IN

article.description: Michael Thompson scored a tournament-record 35 points and Drew Crawford added 15 Thursday, leading Northwestern to a 75-65 victory over Minnesota in the first round of the Big Ten tournament.

related.description: Tubby Smith says he's working on a contract extension that will keep him in Minneapolis long-term despite speculation he could take another job after the season.
related.linkText: Smith working on extension to stay in Minnesota
related.title: Big Ten tournament: Minnesota coach Tubby Smith working on contract extension
related.headline: Tubby Smith working on extension

article.headline: Michael Thompson nets tourney-record 35 as Northwestern beats Minnesota
article.story: INDIANAPOLIS -- Michael Thompson scored a tournament-record 35 points and Drew Crawford added 15 Thursday, leading Northwestern to a 75-65 victory over Minnesota in the first round of the Big Ten tournament. Northwestern (18-12) now faces No. 1 Ohio State (29-2) in the first game of Friday's quarterfinals. Minnesota (17-14) has lost 10 of its last 11. The Gophers were led by Trevor Mbakwe with 19 points and Ralph Sampson III with 12. But it was Thompson who stole the show by breaking the tourney scoring record of 33 set by Purdue's Brian Cardinal. The Wildcats turned the game with a quick flurry midway through the second half. It started with Alex Marcotullio's 3-pointer, and the 13-1 run ended when Marcotullio put in a layup to make it 55-45 with 8:57 left. It's the third time in 18 years Tubby Smith did not win at least one conference tournament game.
